args: Laranoa lives in a forest village to the west.\nOne day, she will become the next chief.
Her duties require her to lead and unify\nall the people of the village. However...
What should we do with the game\nwe caught earlier, Laranoa?
Smoke it and store it, please. Oh, but\nfirst cut some off for us to eat now!
The elders wish to meet with you regarding\nthe upcoming ritual. And afterwards, there\nare many more who would bend your ear.
They'll all get their turn, but I'm busy\nat the moment. Can you let them know\nI'll see 'em later?
The sentries are saying their arrows\nhaven't been getting replenished lately.
Didn't we decide on a rotation for that\nthe other day? Hold on, I'll check...
They ask to be prioritized. Additionally,\nan envoy from a nearby village has arrived.\nHe claims his business is urgent.
Wait, hold on—one thing at a time!
You must be more organized, Laranoa.
Save me your excuses. If you persist\nas you are, you will never become chief.
There's more to being a leader than\njust ordering people around, huh?\n*munch*
Definitely. You need to be aware of every\ndevelopment, big or small, as well as each\nperson's individual concerns and issues.
See, YOU get it. Nobody else seems\nto though.
I know I'm not doing the best job at\nthe moment, but the chief didn't\nneed to be so harsh...
Isn't it enough that I'm TRYING?!\nRrrgh! *munch* *slurp*
Why won't you just admit fault and\napologize, Luca? You're wasting\nboth of our time.
Sylas, hey! Any chance you wanna\ncome work for me?
You know well how busy my\naromatics research keeps me.\nI wouldn't have the time.
I'd gathered some strawberries to keep\nme sated during my research, you see.
My eyes were away for mere moments—\nbut when I looked back, they were gone.
I'm innocent, I tell ya! Innocent!
You're the only soul in this castle capable\nof such guile. Of that I am QUITE certain.
This is far from your first foray\ninto treachery. You purloined\nmy sandwich when—
We were KIDS! I wouldn't do that\nnow—tell him, {player_name}!
I think we first need to—
Admit your guilt, Luca! Act swiftly,\nand your castigation will be merciful.
I'm tellin' ya, I didn't do it!
Ummm... Sylas? Where was it you\nleft those strawberries?
The kitchen. They were of the very same\nripeness as the ones you are currently...\nAh. I see.
Ohmigosh, I am SO sorry.\nI swear I didn't know!
I thought Cleo had just left them out\nfor everyone...
What'd I tell ya?! If you apologize,\nI'll let ya off with only minor\ncasti...whatever!
Great. You're forgiven. But Laranoa,\nhow'd ya not even think to ask\nbefore ya ate those strawberries?
I... I don't know. I'm sorry.
I mean, come on. How the heck are\nyou gonna be chief if ya act like that?
I don't have to take that from YOU, Luca.
C'mon, I'M the one Sylas almost smacked!
That doesn't give you the right to question\nmy ability to be chief! AT ALL!
Whoa, hey, I was just thinkin' about\nyour future.
Hah, wow... So I'm so hopeless even\nmy FRIENDS don't believe in me now?
I'm TRYING! I'M DOING MY BEST!
It was bad enough having the chief scold\nme, but now you too? I'm outta here.
Hey, wait! ...Man, I think I really\nmessed things up.
She's been having a hard time lately.\nIt can be overwhelming when everyone\nrelies on you so much.
Aw, jeez... I better go find her\nand apologize.
Wait. If you go after her now, it will only\nmake things worse.
Someone else should speak with her first.
Oh? Hm... Yes, I think that's a good idea.
I was worried about you. We all were.
Luca really wasn't trying to attack you\nwhen he said those things. I'm sure\nhe'd like to tell you as much himself.
*sigh* I know. He always speaks without\nthinking, and I KNOW that, so I really\nshouldn't have blown up like I did.
His words just hit a little close to home,\nI guess.
I'm trying as hard as I can to be someone\npeople can depend on, but lately it almost\nfeels like I'm going backwards.
I'm scared that if I don't start improving\nsoon, everyone's gonna give up on me.
I just...really don't know if I'm cut out\nto be chief.
Some people are born leaders; some have\nto work at it.
I think if you just envision the leader\nyou want to be, and work toward\nit little by little, you'll get there.
The leader I want to be...
Right. Besides, I think the reason you're\nso uneasy is because you really care for\nthe people you're leading.
I do. And I think you're more than fit\nto be your village's next chief.
I still have a lot to learn about being\na leader myself—so let's work toward\nour goals together.
Heh, all right. I might lack experience,\nbut as long as I know where I want to\nend up, I can keep moving forward.
One step at a time. Together with you.
Do you feel a little better?
I do. Thanks, {player_name}.\nI guess I better go apologize to Luca...
I'm glad to see you've calmed down,\nLaranoa.
What the—Sylas? Luca?!\nYou guys followed me too?!
I didn't realize what you were goin'\nthrough... But even then, I was a\nturbo jerk. Can you forgive me?
I'm the one who should be apologizing;\nI started this whole mess. I'm sorry, Luca!
I'm glad you two made up.
Hey, how bout I go gather some more\nstrawberries from the forest?
Me and Sylas'll come too—we can make\nit a competition! Just like old times.
Heh. I suppose indulging nostalgia\ncan be beneficial from time to time.\nWhat say you, Laranoa?
If you guys are up for it, count me in!
